      • verify

        public FingerprintVerifyResult verify(FingerprintSecurityLevel securityLevel,
                             byte[] featureData1,
                             byte[] featureData2)
                               throws FingerprintException
        Verify one feature from another (from database).If the value of VerifyResult.error is 0, it means no error has occurred, so you can get the similarity value and check if they are matched. Otherwise it means an error occurred and you cannot get similarity or match results. Aratek TrustFingrt SDK provides 5 security levels. The relationship with Matching threshold,
        Parameters:
        securityLevel - Security Level, has five levels: 1 to 5. Higher, safer securityLevel Recommend to use level 4. (See Enumeration FingerprintSecurityLevel)
        featureData1 - Fingerprint feature data
        featureData2 - Fingerprint feature data
        Returns:
        Verify result. (See Class FingerprintSecurityLevel )
        Throws:
        FingerprintException
